lead_paragraph: DEATH OF A REVOLUTIONARY SOLDIER.--The Cleveland Plain Dealer chronicles the departure from this world, of another of the old soldiers of the Revolution Moses Warren, of Warrensville, Ohio. He was in his ninety-second year, having been born in 1760 fifteen years before the commencement of the Revolutionary War.
